snippet: Builders broke ground on fewer houses and apartment complexes in August, but homebuilding still seems much stronger than a year ago.
abstract: Commerce Dept reports that housing starts fell 3 percent in August, possible sign that housing market may be leveling off after accelerating for much of 2015.
lead_paragraph: Builders broke ground on fewer houses and apartment complexes in August, but homebuilding still seems much stronger than a year ago.

headline.main: Housing Starts Fell in August, but Remained on Pace for Recovery
headline.print_headline: Fewer Starts in Housing, but Analysts Are Upbeat
